timeline.bodyText:
Here is the only missing condition in term of coverage (owner == null probably).
I feel that we might be missing the point. For me, the only way to have a missing owner is to have a symbol not correctly resolved, and, therefore, marked as being unknown (package symbols can not occur here). I would consequently only test like this:
return !symbol.isUnknown() && (symbol.isTypeSymbol() || symbol.owner().isTypeSymbol());
Now, in order to cover it, simply create a test file under java-checks-test-sources/src/main/files/non-compiling/checks, and then add a test such as:
  @Test
  void test_non_compiling() {
    JavaCheckVerifier.newVerifier()
      .onFile(nonCompilingTestSourcesPath("checks/VisibleForTestingUsageCheck.java"))
      .withCheck(new VisibleForTestingUsageCheck())
      .verifyIssues();
  }
And as a test code something like:
class VisibleForTestingUsageCheck {
  @com.google.common.annotations.VisibleForTesting 
  void bar() { }

  void foo() {
    unknown(); // Compliant
  }
}

class VisibleForTestingUsageCheck2 {
  void qix() {
    new VisibleForTestingUsageCheck()
      .bar(); // Noncompliant
  }
}

